    <h1>8.8 &quot;Stop &amp; Disable&quot; behaviour</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h2 id=3D"id-8.8&quot;Stop&amp;Disable&quot;behaviour-Question">Que=
stion</h2>
<p>What should happen when a DAD is running and the user disables the DAD?&=
nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"id-8.8&quot;Stop&amp;Disable&quot;behaviour-CurrentBehavior">Curr=
ent Behavior</h2>
<p>RAS backend sets the Enabled bit to false in the DAD, writes to database=
 and then sends a rabbitmq message to DAE notifying him of change thorugh a=
n IDefinitionDisabled message.&nbsp;</p>
<p>DAE receives this IDefinitionDisabled message, finds relevant DADRunner =
and tells it to add a new task to his task queue that reloads the DAD from =
database. It also schedules a new run, which will do nothing because the DA=
D will detect that it is disabled.&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"id-8.8&quot;Stop&amp;Disable&quot;behaviour-NewBehavior">New Beha=
vior</h2>
<p>The RAS Backend sets the Enabled bit to false in the DAD, writes to data=
base. The RAS backend then sends a DisableAbort message to the DAE. DAE rec=
eives the message and dispatches it to the relevant DADRunner for that DAD.=
 DADRunner fires the cancellationtoken he's been giving out to his tasks. R=
unning DAD's regularly check if their cancellationtoken has expired during =
their execution. They stop execution if cancellationtoken has fired.&nbsp;<=
/p>
<p>Any reload tasks contained in the queue need to proceed normally without=
 looking at the cancellationToken. If we cancel these too, the DAD will not=
 be reloaded&nbsp; and it will remain in the Enabled rather than the new Di=
sabled state. it's possible that at the time the cancellationtoken was fire=
d the task queue looks something like this:</p>
<ol>
<li>Run (currently executing)</li>
<li>Reload</li>
<li>Run</li>
</ol>
<p>3. Run will have received the same cancellationtoken as 1. Run. So when =
the DADRunner finally starts executing 3. Run, his cancellationtoken will h=
ave already fired. This is not an issue however, because it will detect tha=
t the Enabled flag has been set to false.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Finally, the DADRunner creates a new CancellationToken he can give to ne=
wly created run tasks.&nbsp;</p>
    </div>
